# Wikipedia Content Summarizer

This Python script extracts content from a Wikipedia page about hair loss and uses the OpenAI GPT-3.5 model to generate a summary of the content in no more than three paragraphs.

## Requirements

- Python 3.x
- `requests` library (`pip install requests`)
- `beautifulsoup4` library (`pip install beautifulsoup4`)
- An OpenAI API key

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:

    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/your_username/your_repository.git
    ```

2. Install dependencies:

    ```bash
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

3. Set up environment variables:

    You need to set up an environment variable named `openaikey` with your OpenAI API key. You can obtain an API key by signing up at https://openai.com.

## Usage

1. Run the script:

    ```bash
    python wikipedia_content_summarizer.py
    ```

2. The script will scrape the content from the Wikipedia page about hair loss and generate a summary using the GPT-3.5 model. The summary will be printed to the console.

